                    "text": "> > I also think this is a good idea, although this does mean that anything with > > a wide-ish, or long-ish screen may expose checker-boarding while the finger > > is down.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> \n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "> The finger can't be down for more than the width or height of the screen, so > as long as we already have one screen width and height in the direction of > the pan that shouldn't be a problem\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "But the problem is most devices have a 2k texture limit and we don't do tiling, so any device with a dimension greater than 1024, it'll be possible to pan to the checkerboard. ", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "Either way, this is still an unlikely situation, and one would've hoped that the devices coming with 1920x1200 screens will have a 4k texture limit.\n", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }
            ], 
